# .cursorrules
# Binance Market Intelligence Agent

## Project Overview
AI agent that fetches live Binance market data, detects unusual movers,
searches latest news, and uses Groq LLaMA 3.3 to generate a professional
market briefing. Displayed via a dark-themed Streamlit dashboard.

## Architecture
- agent.py  → Core pipeline (Binance API → News → Groq AI → structured dict)
- app.py    → Streamlit dashboard consuming agent.py output

## Code Rules
- All functions must have clear docstrings
- Use type hints throughout
- Groq API key loaded from .env (never hardcoded)
- Keep functions single-purpose, max 40 lines each
- Print status messages with emoji in CLI mode

## Security
- NEVER hardcode API keys
- .env and .streamlit/secrets.toml are in .gitignore
- Use os.getenv() for all credentials

## Streamlit Rules
- All styling via st.markdown with custom CSS
- Dark theme: #080c14 background, #38bdf8 accent
- Font: Space Mono (monospace) + Inter (body)
- No use of st.dataframe or default Streamlit components for main UI

## Binance API
- Uses public endpoint only: https://api.binance.com/api/v3/ticker/24hr
- No authentication required
- MOVER_THRESHOLD = 2.0% for significant movement detection
